        <h4>Who are we?</h4>
        <p>
            Rotary Club of Indore Meghdoot, a club under Rotary International, was formed on October 25th, 1994 at Indore. In the past 19 years RC Meghdoot has grown from strength to strength and has carved a name for it in undertaking major service project in and around Indore.
        </p>
            <h4>How many Paul Harris Fellow in our club?</h4>
            <p>The Paul Harris Fellow program recognizes individuals who contribute, or who have contributions made in their name, of $1,000 to The Rotary Foundation of Rotary International. Currently, Rotray Indore Meghdoot has 70 Paul Harris Fellows and still counting.</p>
            <p>The honor was established in 1957 to show appreciation for contributions that support our Annual Fund, PolioPlus, or an approved Foundation grant.</p>
    <h4>What are we Donating to the community worldwide?</h4>
            <p>Donating to Rotary means clean water and sanitation. Health and hope in areas that were once ravaged by diseases like polio. Economic development and new opportunities. Your financial help makes all this happen, and more. When you give to The Rotary Foundation, you fuel our service projects - projects that eradicate polio, promote peace, and improve developing communities.</p>
<p>Rotray Indore Meghdoot is donating 1,000 USD to Paul Harris Fellow for year 2017-2018. Our contribution is to make a positive change into once life and way of living.</p>
            <h4>What kind of Grants we run?</h4>
            <p>Rotary members contribute their skills, expertise, and resources to help solve some of the world’s toughest problems. From providing clean water to promoting peace worldwide, Rotary Foundation grants bring service project ideas to life.</p>
            <p>Our club is running a grant to provide school furnitures to those private or government owned schools where children are deprived of proper sitting and studying arrangements.</p>
            <h5>Steps to apply for a grant</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>Learn about our <a href="https://my.rotary.org/en/take-action/apply-grants/global-grants">global</a> and <a href="https://my.rotary.org/en/take-action/apply-grants/district-grants">district</a> grants.</li>
                <li>Get <a href="https://my.rotary.org/en/take-action/apply-grants/qualification">qualified.</a></li>
                <li>Start and manage your application at the <a href="https://my.rotary.org/en/user/login?destination=secure/application/236">Rotary Grant Center</a></li>
            </ul>
            <h4>When do we meet?</h4>
            <p>We meet periodically to monitor and shape our initiatives and efforts. The kind of meeting we hold regularly are:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Family Meeting</li>
                <li>Business Meeting</li>
                <li>Board Meeting</li>
                <li>Speaker Meeting</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>What are our achievements?</h4>
            <p>Every year each district holds an Award Night to falicitate clubs based on their services and hardwork. For year 2017-2018, we have earned the following awards:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Best Club Award</li>
                <li>Best Bulletin Award</li>
                <li>Best Secretary Award</li>
                <li>Best Vibrant Award</li>
            </ul>
